POLICE arrested more than 700 suspects in Limpopo at the weekend. Spokesman Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said 789 suspects were bust for various offences. Ngoepe said 27 of the suspects were illegal immigrants aged between 21 and 56. He said the operation started on Friday night and ended yesterday morning. “All the suspects have already started appearing in different magistrates courts around the province,” Ngoepe told the People’s Paper. Cops involved in the raids and arrests came from: ) operational command centre ) public order policing unit   ) tactical response team   ) detective, K9 and crime prevention units.